ed well  Total Returns  net of fees      Team A S P 400 Team B S P 500 30 Sept  05   31 March  08 11 15  8 82  4 60  7 64  30 Sept  07   31 March  08 0 01   8 13  2 35   6 91  In November 2007  twelve members along with the advisors traveled on the sixth annual trip to New York City  The group attended a number of informative meetings hosted by a variety of firms  including AllianceBerstein  Bloomberg  Goode Partners  and TM Capital  The NYC alumni again hosted the cadets to dinner  In March 2008  four cadets and the advisors attended RISE VIII  Redefining Investment Strategy Education  at the University of Dayton  Attended by over 2000 domestic and international students and faculty from over 200 colleges and universities  RISE brings leading investment professionals together with the students and faculty in an exciting and interactive learning environment  RISE offers our cadets exposure to Wall Street professional investors and portfolio managers and members of other college and university student investment clubs  Spring 2008 Newsletter  AACSB Accreditation  Field Test BU  Mission Statement  Faculty Research  Speakers  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  Bank Field Trip  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  Stay Connected Information   Social Sciences Economics   Business Home Degrees   Programs Courses Economics Newsletter Departmental Activities Policies   Forms About ECBU Faculty Open House Presentation Senior Exit Survey Alumni  97    07 survey Donna Potter Executive Secretary P   540  464 7234 F   540  464 7005 Virginia Military Institute 345 Scott Shipp Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact ECBU  Information   Social Sciences Economics   Business Home Degrees   Programs Courses Economics Newsletter Departmental Activities Policies   Forms About ECBU Faculty Open House Presentation Senior Exit Survey Alumni  97    07 survey Donna Potter Executive Secretary P   540  464 7234 F   540  464 7005 Virginia Military Institute 345 Scott Shipp Hall Lexing