B had  105 650 65  As of 31 March 2007  team A had  112 162 25 and team B had  103 220 02  Relative to their respective benchmarks  the Standard and Poor s 400 Mid cap for group A and the Standard and Poor s 500 Large cap for group B  both teams have performed well  Total Returns  net of fees      Team A S P 400 Team B S P 500 30 Sept  05   31 March  08 11 15  8 82  4 60  7 64  30 Sept  07   31 March  08 0 01   8 13  2 35   6 91  In November 2007  twelve members along with the advisors traveled on the sixth annual trip to New York City  The group attended a number of informative meetings hosted by a variety of firms  including AllianceBerstein  Bloomberg  Goode Partners  and TM Capital  The NYC alumni again hosted the cadets to dinner  In March 2008  four cadets and the advisors attended RISE VIII  Redefining Investment Strategy Education  at the University of Dayton  Attended by over 2000 domestic and international students and faculty from over 200 colleges and universities  RISE brings leading investment professionals together with the students and faculty in an exciting and interactive learning environment  RISE offers our cadets exposure to Wall Street professional investors and portfolio managers and members of other college and university student investment clubs  Spring 2008 Newsletter  AACSB Accreditation  Field Test BU  Mission Statement  Faculty Research  Speakers  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  Bank Field Trip  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  Stay Connected Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   Cadet Investment Group Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   Cadet Investment Group Home Academics Areas of Study Social Science Economics   Business Cadet Investment Group      Cadet Investment Group The Cadet Investment Group  CIG  was founded in 1986 by the VMI Foundation  The group s mission is to learn about investing  To do this  members serve as investment analysts and portfolio managers  Divided into two teams  each team has its own investment style and methodology  Team A focuses on middle sized growth stocks while team B invests only in large capitalization value stocks  CIG is open to all 3rd  2nd and 1st class cadets  without regard to major  Faculty advisors to the CIG are Col  Cliff West and Col  Bob Moreschi  Each team had  101 000 under management on 30 September 2005  As of March 31 2008  team A had  112 260 32 under management while team B had  105 650 65  As of 31 March 2007  team A had  112 162 25 and team B had  103 220 02  Relative to their respective benchmarks  the Standard and Poor s 400 Mid cap for group A and the Standard and Poor s 500 Large cap for group B  both teams have performed well  Total Returns  net of fees      Team A S P 400 Team B S P 500 30 Sept  05   31 March  08 11 15  8 82  4 60  7 64  30 Sept  07   31 March  08 0 01   8 13  2 35   6 91  In November 2007  twelve members along with the advisors traveled on the sixth annual trip to New York City  The group attended a number of informative meetings hosted by a variety of firms  including AllianceBerstein  Bloomberg  Goode Partners  and TM Capital  The NYC alumni again hosted the cadets to dinner  In March 2008  four cadets and the advisors attended RISE VIII  Redefining Investment Strategy Education  at the University of Dayton  Attended by over 2000 domestic and international students and faculty from over 200 colleges and universities  RISE brings leading investment professionals together with the students and faculty in an exciting and interactive learning environment  RISE offers our cadets exposure to Wall Street professional investors and portfolio managers and members of other college and university student investment clubs Cadet Investment Group The Cadet Investment Group  CIG  was founded in 1986 by the VMI Foundation  The group s mission is to learn about investing  To do this  members serve as investment analysts and portfol